  guideId: rubik3x3.beginner
  language: 
  family: 0
  title: "Beginner's Guide to the 3\xD73 Rubik's Cube"
  description: Learn the beginner method by understanding *why* each move works,
    not just memorizing algorithms.
  sections:
  - rid: 2637682859175837784
  - rid: 2637682859175837785
  references:
    version: 2
    RefIds:
    - rid: 2637682859175837784
      type: {class: GuideSection, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Before We Begin
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 0
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves: []
        nodes:
        - rid: 2637682859175837786
        - rid: 2637682859175837787
        - rid: 2637682859175837788
        - rid: 2637682859175837789
    - rid: 2637682859175837785
      type: {class: GuideSection, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: The White Cross
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 0
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves: []
        nodes:
        - rid: 2637682859175837790
        - rid: 2637682859175837791
        - rid: 2637682859175837792
        - rid: 2637682859175837793
        - rid: 2637682859175837794
        - rid: 2637682859175837795
    - rid: 2637682859175837786
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Meet the Cube
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - 'text:'
          - '"Center'
          - pieces
          - never
          - move
          - relative
          - to
          - each
          - other.
          - They
          - determine
          - the
          - color
          - of
          - each
          - face."
        body: 'Before learning to solve the cube, let''s become familiar with its
          pieces.

          

          A Rubik''s Cube is made of three different
          kinds of pieces:

          

          - Centers

          - Edges

          -
          Corners'
        actions: []
    - rid: 2637682859175837787
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Centers Define the Faces
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - highlight
          - centers
        body: "Notice that every face has one center piece.\r\n\r\nThe white center
          always belongs opposite the yellow center.\r\n\r\nLikewise:\r\n\r\n- Blue
          \u2194 Green\r\n- Red \u2194 Orange\r\n\r\nThese relationships never change."
        actions: []
    - rid: 2637682859175837788
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Edge Pieces
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - highlight
          - edges
        body: 'Edge pieces have exactly two stickers.

          

          Every
          edge belongs between two centers.'
        actions: []
    - rid: 2637682859175837789
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Corner Pieces
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - highlight
          - corners
        body: 'Corner pieces have three stickers.

          

          Each corner
          belongs between three centers.'
        actions: []
    - rid: 2637682859175837790
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Our First Goal
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - state
          - solved_cross_demo
        body: 'The first milestone is called the **White Cross**.

          

          This
          means placing the four white edge pieces around the white center.

          

          More
          importantly, the side colors must also match their neighboring centers.'
        actions: []
    - rid: 2637682859175837791
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: A Correct Cross
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - highlight
          - solved_cross
        body: 'This is what a finished white cross looks like.

          

          Notice
          that every edge matches **two** center pieces.

          

          Many
          beginners stop after matching white.

          

          Don''t.

          

          Matching
          the side colors is equally important.'
        actions: []
    - rid: 2637682859175837792
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Finding a White Edge
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - highlight
          - edge_white_blue
        body: 'Let''s solve one edge together.

          

          This lesson
          starts from a fixed puzzle state.

          

          Look around
          the cube.

          

          Can you find the white-blue edge?'
        actions: []
    - rid: 2637682859175837793
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Bring the Edge Above Its Destination
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - highlight
          - blue_center
        body: 'First, rotate the upper layer until the blue sticker lines up with
          the blue center.

          

          Now the edge is positioned above
          the slot where it belongs.'
        actions:
        - rid: 2637682859175837796
        - rid: 2637682859175837797
    - rid: 2637682859175837794
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Insert the Edge
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 1
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves:
          - highlight
          - solved_edge
        body: 'Rotate the front face twice.

          

          The edge is
          now solved.

          

          Notice that both colors match their
          centers.'
        actions:
        - rid: 2637682859175837798
        - rid: 2637682859175837799
    - rid: 2637682859175837795
      type: {class: GuideBlock, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        title: Recap
        stateSetup:
          isEnabled: 0
          mode: 0
          scrambleMoves: []
        body: 'To solve an edge of the white cross:

          

          - Find
          the edge.

          - Match its side color with the correct center.

          -
          Insert it into the white face.

          

          We''ll repeat this
          idea for the remaining edge cases.'
        actions: []
    - rid: 2637682859175837796
      type: {class: TutorialMove, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        moveId: U
    - rid: 2637682859175837797
      type: {class: TutorialMove, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        moveId: U
    - rid: 2637682859175837798
      type: {class: TutorialMove, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        moveId: F
    - rid: 2637682859175837799
      type: {class: TutorialMove, ns: Cubetorial.Tutorials.Scripts, asm: Cubetorial.Tutorials}
      data:
        moveId: F
